---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="index_workspace — ArchLens"
  description="Analyze Java project roots and build the ArchLens architecture graph through six extraction passes."
>
  <section class="tool-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="tool-page-header">
        <h1 class="tool-page-title">index_workspace</h1>
        <span class="tool-page-badge">Index</span>
      </div>

      <p class="tool-page-intro">
        The entry point for every ArchLens session. Point it at one or more Java project
        roots and it runs six extraction passes — components, injection dependencies, call
        graph, data-flow tracing, container inference, and external system inference —
        then stores the result as a TinkerGraph. Every other tool reads from that graph.
        Re-run it any time sources change.
      </p>

      <h2 class="tool-section-label">Arguments</h2>
      <table class="arg-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Name</th>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th>Required</th>
            <th>Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>paths</td>
            <td>array</td>
            <td><span class="required-badge">required</span></td>
            <td>Absolute paths to Java project root directories. Each path must contain <code>.java</code> sources or a Maven/Gradle module.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2 class="tool-section-label">Example</h2>
      <div class="terminal-card">
        <div class="terminal-top">
          <span></span><span></span><span></span>
          <strong>tools/call</strong>
        </div>
        <pre><code>{`{
  "name": "index_workspace",
  "arguments": {
    "paths": ["/home/user/projects/my-java-app"]
  }
}`}</code></pre>
      </div>

      <h2 class="tool-section-label">Output</h2>
      <p class="tool-page-intro">
        A summary of what was indexed: number of applications found, components, entrypoints,
        interfaces, injection edges, call edges, data-flow paths, and containers. The graph
        is cached under <code>.archlens-cache/</code> in the server's working directory.
        Subsequent tool calls read from this cache without re-indexing. Alongside this text,
        the response's <code>structuredContent</code> carries the same app/component/entrypoint
        counts as JSON.
      </p>

      <h2 class="tool-section-label">Related tools</h2>
      <div class="related-pills">
        <a href="/#tools" class="related-pill">list_apps</a>
        <a href="/#tools" class="related-pill">find_entrypoints</a>
        <a href="/tools/trace-data-flow" class="related-pill">trace_data_flow</a>
        <a href="/tools/query-architecture-graph" class="related-pill">query_architecture_graph</a>
      </div>

      <a href="/#tools" class="tool-back-link">← All tools</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
